The Baker by Nature Comprehensive Tropical Smoothie
This final candidate is a "master" of the tropical category because it refuses to settle for just one or two fruits. It incorporates papaya and lime to reach a level of flavor complexity that others lack.31
The recipe requires 1 cup each of frozen mango and pineapple, 1/2 cup of papaya, and 2 large ripe bananas.31 The liquid base is 3/4 cup each of orange juice and coconut milk.31 The "master" addition is the tablespoon of lime juice and a teaspoon of lime zest, which provides the necessary acidity and aromatic oils to balance the dense tropical sweetness.31
From a home chef perspective, the lime is the "secret weapon" that wakes up all the other flavors.31 The use of canned coconut milk is recommended for its high-fat content, which creates a "thick, creamy, and utterly refreshing" texture that can stand up to the high acidity of the citrus.